Assign environment variables to a list

Source: R/make_branch.R
make_branch.Rd

A function that may be called by lapply() to assign all of the variables in the given environment to slots within a list. This

make_branch(
  analyst = "",
  study_name = "",
  movement_type = "",
  years = 1,
  seasons = 1,
  ages = 1,
  extended_plus_group = 1,
  first_year = 1,
  last_year = 1,
  season = 1,
  recruitment = "",
  growth = "",
  selectivity = "",
  movement = data.frame(1),
  natural_mortality = data.frame(1),
  fishing_mortality = data.frame(0.2),
  area = "",
  population = "",
  likelihood_component = "",
  fleet = "",
  survey = ""
)

Arguments

...

each of the arguments needs to exist in your working directory. If they do, they will be assigned to a list that is then returned.
